e appear to be Shakespearean plays.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-23T18:36:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20150623025348/http://compsoc.dur.ac.uk/whitespace\">Whitespace</a> - Use only white-characters (space, tabs and newlines).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-23T18:36:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://esolangs.org\">Esolang</a> - Wiki of esoteric programming languages and related Resources.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-23T18:36:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/gvx/suzy\">Suzy</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/gvx/suzy\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">7</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":7,\"repo\":\"gvx/suzy\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - 3D language inspired in Befunge.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-10T22:12:22.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/angrykoala/chuckscript\">ChuckScript</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/angrykoala/chuckscript\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">30</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":30,\"repo\":\"angrykoala/chuckscript\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Unary-based language, where the code is a single number.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://esolangs.org/wiki/DNA-Sharp\">DNA#</a> - Language based on the structure of the DNA.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://lolcode.org\">LolCode</a> - Language with keywords based on the lolcat meme expressions.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.dangermouse.net/esoteric/ook.html\">Ook!</a> - Brainfuck-based language, where the commands are orangutan words.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://esolangs.org/wiki/Unary\">Unary</a> - Brainfuck-based language where all the commands are 0.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://velato.net\">Velato</a> - Language that uses MIDI files as source, programs are defined by the pitch and order of notes.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.dangermouse.net/esoteric/whenever.html\">Whenever</a> - Language that does things whenever it wants.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esoteric_programming_language\">Wikipedia/Esoteric programming languages</a> - Wikipedia list of esoteric languages.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-14T11:18:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http